issue.title: [Feature] T5 AWQ support on RTX 20XX? (i.e. CUDA arch 7.5)
issue.body:
### Checklist

- [x] 1. If the issue you raised is not a feature but a question, please raise a discussion at https://github.com/mit-han-lab/nunchaku/discussions/new/choose. Otherwise, it will be closed.
- [x] 2. I will do my best to describe the issue in English.

### Motivation

I was playing with this just now, using the latest dev nightly release of Nunchaku: https://huggingface.co/mit-han-lab/nunchaku-t5

It works *surprisingly* well on my 4090 - producing images that might even be better than `t5xxl_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled.safetensors`. Quality seems to be at least as high based on my initial tests.

But testing on my 2070 GPU (old laptop), it gives a "This kernel is not supported on your GPU", which I think might be due to AWQ not being supported on 20XX series? E.g.:

https://github.com/mit-han-lab/nunchaku/blob/6098c41946efd9e0f344d0c50741abef2f2f7ff9/src/kernels/awq/gemm_awq.cu#L381-L384

https://github.com/mit-han-lab/nunchaku/blob/6098c41946efd9e0f344d0c50741abef2f2f7ff9/src/kernels/awq/gemv_awq.cu#L109-L113

### Related resources

Not sure if relevant or helpful (probably not), but I noticed some references to CUDA arch older than 800 in `llm-awq`:

https://github.com/mit-han-lab/llm-awq/blob/7016bbeca006a573705491a651bf31e433e4e379/awq/kernels/csrc/w8a8/utils.cuh#L97

https://github.com/mit-han-lab/llm-awq/blob/7016bbeca006a573705491a651bf31e433e4e379/awq/kernels/csrc/quantization_new/gemm/semaphore.h#L64

https://github.com/mit-han-lab/llm-awq/blob/7016bbeca006a573705491a651bf31e433e4e379/awq/kernels/csrc/attention/decoder_masked_multihead_attention_utils.h#L265

https://github.com/mit-han-lab/llm-awq/blob/7016bbeca006a573705491a651bf31e433e4e379/awq/kernels/csrc/attention/decoder_masked_multihead_attention_template.hpp#L427

https://github.com/mit-han-lab/llm-awq/blob/7016bbeca006a573705491a651bf31e433e4e379/awq/kernels/csrc/attention/cuda_bf16_fallbacks.cuh#L39

https://github.com/mit-han-lab/llm-awq/blob/7016bbeca006a573705491a651bf31e433e4e379/awq/kernels/csrc/attention/cuda_bf16_fallbacks.cuh#L140

comment.body:
@lmxyy Yep, I'm testing in ComfyUI, and I printed the dtype right before [these lines](https://github.com/mit-han-lab/ComfyUI-nunchaku/blob/e8e228b39ab1761b3c5ddeb15309496b6fab2827/nodes/models/text_encoder.py#L135-L137): ```py clip.cond_stage_model.t5xxl.transformer = ( transformer.to(device=device, dtype=dtype) if device.type == "cuda" else transformer ) ``` and it's `torch.float16`. I also tried changing [this line](https://github.com/mit-han-lab/ComfyUI-nunchaku/blob/e8e228b39ab1761b3c5ddeb15309496b6fab2827/nodes/models/text_encoder.py#L131C27-L131C49): ```py transformer = NunchakuT5EncoderModel.from_pretrained(model_path) ``` to this: ```py transformer = NunchakuT5EncoderModel.from_pretrained(model_path, torch_dtype=torch.float16) ``` But that didn't help - same error/crash. And I printed the dtype of the `embeds` before they're processed by `self.encoder(input_ids=input_ids, inputs_embeds=embeds, attention_mask=attention_mask)` here: https://github.com/mit-han-lab/ComfyUI-nunchaku/blob/e8e228b39ab1761b3c5ddeb15309496b6fab2827/nodes/models/text_encoder.py#L26 And it's `torch.float16`. The error/crash occurs during the `self.encoder` call and gives these logs in case it's helpful:
Click to see crash logs ``` This kernel is not supported on your GPU This kernel is not supported on your GPU This kernel is not supported on your GPU This kernel is not supported on your GPU terminate called after throwing an instance of 'c10::Error'   what():  CUDA error: unspecified launch failure CUDA kernel errors might be asynchronously reported at some other API call, so the stacktrace below might be incorrect. /opt/conda/lib/python3.11/site-packages/torch/lib/libtorch_cpu.so) frame #13: at::_ops::matmul::call(at::Tensor const&, at::Tensor const&) + 0xcf (0x76ec408bd81f in /opt/conda/lib/python3.11/site-packages/torch/lib/libtorch_cpu.so) frame #14: + 0x47995b (0x76ec527c895b in /opt/conda/lib/python3.11/site-packages/torch/lib/libtorch_python.so) Aborted (core dumped) ```
Just to be clear, as mentioned above, this problem only occurs on my RTX 2070 - it works fine on my RTX 4090. Please let me know if there are any other tests/changes you'd like me to try. Having 4-bit T5 working on 20XX series would be great, because the older GPUs are the ones that tend to have smaller VRAM 🙏
